<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Kallain on 12-13-2001 10:56 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Well,

I don't have AoE experience in the Grey, but I do have melee heavy experience there bothe pre and post patch. The zone is broken and I wont be visiting it again.

My normal group is 60 tank, 60 tank, 60 enchanter, 60 wizard, 59 cleric with the last spot either 60 tank, 60 necro or 60 rogue.

Pre patch I put on over two blue in a single night there. Same group in Velk's or Seb' would normally get me just over a blue and a half. The xp bonus in the zone probably needed to be dropped in the name of tuning.

Post patch night with the same group, I put on 3 blue pixels. My roots were resisted 49 times out of 50 and the two I did get to stick broke after the first tick.

I now see no reason to visit this zone. Before it was both a good xp zone and somewhere to play while a temple raid got together. Now I wont be visiting it for XP and wont even play in it while wiaint on a temple raid. There just isn't any reward for fighting here.

This place will become like Skyfire, you'll zone in and see one group camping a specific item or a single player on his way to somewhere else.

Another useless zone. /sigh


Kallain.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
